Sentencas: The paper describes a mathematical analysis of multi-component diffusion with chemical reaction in the porous materials of high-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The objectives are to clarify the underlying physics, to investigate different modeling approaches and to establish expressions for the cell voltage loss.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The description proceeds from the simplest non-reactive binary diffusion process, through a multi-component analysis with non-reactive diluent gases present, to diffusion in the presence of the water-gas shift chemical reaction.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Using a single average diffusion coefficient, an analytical solution can be found, not only for the limiting cases of frozen and equilibrium water-gas shift chemistry but also for the general non-equilibrium situation.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A Damkohler number is identified and it is shown that shift equilibrium is not necessarily preserved in the anode flow.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The non-equilibrium analysis also reveals unusual behavior whereby the molar fluxes become discontinuous in the equilibrium limit while the mole fractions and cell voltage loss approach the limit continuously.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A physically more realistic model based on two diffusion coefficients provides a more detailed description for frozen and equilibrium chemistry but does not yield an explicit non-equilibrium solution.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In all, the analysis provides fundamental insight and quantitative predictions for many of the flow phenomena occurring in the porous materials of SOFCs.
Titulo: An Analytical Study of Diffusion, Chemical Reaction and Voltage Loss in High-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
